About RedHill
RedHill Biopharma Ltd. (NASDAQ: RDHL) (Tel-Aviv Stock Exchange: RDHL) is a specialty biopharmaceutical company primarily focused on the development and commercialization of late clinical-stage, proprietary, orally-administered, small molecule drugs for the treatment of gastrointestinal and inflammatory diseases, including cancer.
The Companyâs current product pipeline includes:
TALICIAâ¢Â - An oral combination therapy forÂ Helicobacter pyloriÂ infection, with positiveÂ results from a first Phase III studyÂ and an ongoing confirmatory Phase III study.
RHB-104Â - An oral combination therapy for the treatment of Crohn's disease with an ongoing first Phase III study, a completed proof-of-concept Phase IIa study for multiple sclerosis,Â and QIDP status for nontuberculous mycobacteria (NTM) infections.
BEKINDAÂ® (RHB-102)Â - AÂ once-daily oral pill formulation of ondansetron with successful top-line results from a Phase III study for acute gastroenteritis and gastritis and an ongoing Phase II study for IBS-D.
RHB-106Â - An encapsulated formulation for bowel preparation licensed to Salix Pharmaceuticals Ltd.
YELIVAÂ® (ABC294640)Â - AÂ Phase II-stage, orally-administered, first-in-class SK2 selective inhibitor targeting multiple oncology, inflammatory and gastrointestinal indications
MESUPRONÂ -Â A Phase II-stage, orally-administered, first-in-class protease inhibitor targeting pancreatic cancer and other solid tumor cancers.Â 
RIZAPORTÂ® (RHB-103)Â - An oral thin film formulation of rizatriptan, for the treatment of acute migraines,Â with a U.S. NDA currently under discussion with the FDA and marketing authorization received in Germany in October 2015.
RedHill promotes two gastrointestinal products in the U.S. - DonnatalÂ®, a prescription oral adjunctive drug used in the treatment of IBS and acute enterocolitis, and EnteraGamÂ®, a medical food intended for the dietary management, under medical supervision, of chronic diarrhea and loose stools.



